<br>
1st.  Thanks Alucard for support and understanding (I really shouldn't have said what I did, I am truly sorry), and I am seeing your view clearly.<br>
<br>
2nd.  Thanks Stinky for your support as well, And the blunt comment that made me laugh a little.<br>
<br>
3rd.  Thanks for writing an intriguing opinion.  I can see where you are coming from Anyte.  But it is also true that women... And don't take this as an insult (I don't know why you would)... where treated EXTREMELY poorly in the Greek and Roman times, in fact most women of the past did not have much choice in society, and many (if not all) were not artists... Already you can see the &quot;Man's&quot; influence.  Also, I'm sorry I was not there for your post, just consider this one my trip into the subject. Last of all I am not for complete banning of Nudity just stricter regulations over what the newbies draw, and I request that you read what I had to say on the matter, because you seem to be missing my point (tell you honestly you can kinda' disregard my point entirely cause its not quite yet decided).<br>
<br>
Rogue Yun<br>
