<br>
Let me say this.  Take another look at ancient art and you will see that a large percentage of it is MALE nudes.  This isn't about sexism ... it's about nudity in art and nudity in art has ALWAYS been there.  Female nudity is more predominant in art today than it was in ancient cultures.  I draw both male and female nudes, though I don't share them.  And ... in case you haven't guessed (some people don't make the connection between the avatar, the name, and myself) I am female.<br>
<br>
I do not like the blatant eroticism in the art that is posted on this board at times, but to deny those who see nude art as eroticism would be to deny the serious artists who see nudity as purely art.   <p><br><br><p align=center><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><font color=red><b><i>Read my profile </b></a><font size=1>and find out what kind of top secret stuff I've been up to.  Come on!  It'll be fun.</font><font color=blue>
