<br>
I don't think I can make clear my position on eroticism in art.  I've seen the works of Boris Vallejo and others like him and am not bothered by the work at all.  I rather like Vallejo's work.  I'm not necessarily bothered by eroticism in cartoons either.  I think it's more the ill proportioned, in your face, look at my HUGE breasts, see my behind as I spread my legs or bend over type of art that gets to me.  Hmm ... I guess it just boils down to what I think is tacky and what is not.  I think Boris Vallejo does some very nice work and I don't think the way he depicts women is degrading, while I have seen many drawings on this board of females with breasts that are seriously the size of their head, and again with the tacky cropped tops and the short short skirts.  Again, it's all about the artists intent.  (and i only pick on the artists here because it's the work i'm most familiar with that i don't like - i don't see a lot of stuff out there like that) <p><br><br><p align=center><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN"><font color=red><b><i>Read my profile </b></a><font size=1>and find out what kind of top secret stuff I've been up to.  Come on!  It'll be fun.</font><font color=blue>
